We finally hit Sub-50! After more than a month of grinding I've got there at last, with 26 seconds to spare! I think this run went really well except for Chapter 5, where I absolutely fumbled the A and B sides, which is quite annoying because if I had got my average Temple time of about 6:40, I would have a run in the 47-48 minute range. 

But aside from that, I hit PBs in Ridge, Reflection and Summit, getting my first ever Sub-5 Ridge and Sub-9 Reflection, so can't complain too much! And of course, there was plenty of chokage in some of the later levels that if optimized could easily knock minutes off my run, but that's all par for the course when it comes to speedrunning. 

I'm very glad I've finally broken the 50 minute barrier, but I think it will be quite some time before I start nearing Sub-40, so my goal now is to study the Programmatic guides (and Average Imposter's video when it comes out) and improve my ILs to the point that I can start consistently hitting Sub-45, and then we'll see where we go from there

I've been playing Celeste for about 9 months, and I've been speedrunning it for at least half that time. This is my first recorded run, where I manage to complete the game in 51 minutes and 5 seconds. This is my Personal Best at the time of writing, and I'm submitting this run to speedrun.com as I want to get into uploading my runs properly.


I only hit sub-hour for the first time about 3 weeks ago, and I've been constantly improving since then. I completed my first sub-hour run in 58:13, then since then I've achieved runs of 56:29, 59:07, 52:31 and 53:30, before finally achieving this run.
